  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: A Vision of Living Beings
      content: '  On July 31[[COMMENT(0)]] of my thirtieth year,[[COMMENT(1)]] while
        I was with the Judean exiles beside the Kebar River in Babylon, the heavens
        were opened and I saw visions of God. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1a '
        content: Hebrew <b>On the fifth day of the fourth month, </b>of the ancient
          Hebrew lunar calendar. A number of dates in Ezekiel can be cross-checked
          with dates in surviving Babylonian records and related accurately to our
          modern calendar. This event occurred on July 31, 593 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>
      - number: '1:1b '
        content: Or <b>in the thirtieth year.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "This happened during the fifth year of King Jehoiachin\u2019s captivity. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '(The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Ezekiel son
        of Buzi, a priest, beside the Kebar River in the land of the Babylonians,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and he felt the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> take hold of him.)  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:3 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'As I looked, I saw a great storm coming from the north, driving before
        it a huge cloud that flashed with lightning and shone with brilliant light.
        There was fire inside the cloud, and in the middle of the fire glowed something
        like gleaming amber.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:4 '
        content: Or <b>like burnished metal; </b>also in 1:27.
    - title: 
      content: 'From the center of the cloud came four living beings that looked
        human, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'except that each had four faces and four wings. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their legs were straight, and their feet had hooves like those of
        a calf and shone like burnished bronze. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Under each of their four wings I could see human hands. So each of
        the four beings had four faces and four wings. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wings of each living being touched the wings of the beings beside
        it. Each one moved straight forward in any direction without turning around.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Each had a human face in the front, the face of a lion on the right
        side, the face of an ox on the left side, and the face of an eagle at the
        back. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Each had two pairs of outstretched wings\u2014one pair stretched
        out to touch the wings of the living beings on either side of it, and the
        other pair covered its body. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They went in whatever direction the spirit chose, and they moved
        straight forward in any direction without turning around.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The living beings looked like bright coals of fire or brilliant torches,
        and lightning seemed to flash back and forth among them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the living beings darted to and fro like flashes of lightning.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As I looked at these beings, I saw four wheels touching the ground
        beside them, one wheel belonging to each. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wheels sparkled as if made of beryl. All four wheels looked alike
        and were made the same; each wheel had a second wheel turning crosswise within
        it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The beings could move in any of the four directions they faced, without
        turning as they moved. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The rims of the four wheels were tall and frightening, and they were
        covered with eyes all around.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the living beings moved, the wheels moved with them. When they
        flew upward, the wheels went up, too. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The spirit of the living beings was in the wheels. So wherever the
        spirit went, the wheels and the living beings also went. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the beings moved, the wheels moved. When the beings stopped,
        the wheels stopped. When the beings flew upward, the wheels rose up, for
        the spirit of the living beings was in the wheels.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Spread out above them was a surface like the sky, glittering like
        crystal. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Beneath this surface the wings of each living being stretched out
        to touch the others\u2019 wings, and each had two wings covering its body. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As they flew, their wings sounded to me like waves crashing against
        the shore or like the voice of the Almighty[[COMMENT(0)]] or like the shouting
        of a mighty army. When they stopped, they let down their wings. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:24 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Shaddai.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'As they stood with wings lowered, a voice spoke from beyond the crystal
        surface above them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Above this surface was something that looked like a throne made of
        blue lapis lazuli. And on this throne high above was a figure whose appearance
        resembled a man. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'From what appeared to be his waist up, he looked like gleaming amber,
        flickering like a fire. And from his waist down, he looked like a burning
        flame, shining with splendor. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Ezekiel\u2019s Call and Commission"
      content: "  \u201CStand up, son of man,\u201D said the voice. \u201CI want
        to speak with you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Spirit came into me as he spoke, and he set me on my feet. I
        listened carefully to his words. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man,\u201D he said, \u201CI am sending you to the nation
        of Israel, a rebellious nation that has rebelled against me. They and their
        ancestors have been rebelling against me to this very day. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are a stubborn and hard-hearted people. But I am sending you
        to say to them, \u2018This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And whether they listen or refuse to listen\u2014for remember, they
        are rebels\u2014at least they will know they have had a prophet among them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, do not fear them or their words. Don\u2019t be
        afraid even though their threats surround you like nettles and briers and
        stinging scorpions. Do not be dismayed by their dark scowls, even though
        they are rebels. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You must give them my messages whether they listen or not. But they
        won\u2019t listen, for they are completely rebellious! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Son of man, listen to what I say to you. Do not join them in their
        rebellion. Open your mouth, and eat what I give you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I looked and saw a hand reaching out to me. It held a scroll, '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  The voice said to me, \u201CSon of man, eat what I am giving you\u2014eat
        this scroll! Then go and give its message to the people of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I opened my mouth, and he fed me the scroll. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFill your stomach with this,\u201D he said. And when I ate
        it, it tasted as sweet as honey in my mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said, \u201CSon of man, go to the people of Israel and give
        them my messages. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am not sending you to a foreign people whose language you cannot
        understand. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, I am not sending you to people with strange and difficult speech.
        If I did, they would listen! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the people of Israel won\u2019t listen to you any more than they
        listen to me! For the whole lot of them are hard-hearted and stubborn. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But look, I have made you as obstinate and hard-hearted as they are. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have made your forehead as hard as the hardest rock! So don\u2019t
        be afraid of them or fear their angry looks, even though they are rebels.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he added, \u201CSon of man, let all my words sink deep into
        your own heart first. Listen to them carefully for yourself. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then go to your people in exile and say to them, \u2018This is what
        the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says!\u2019 Do this whether they
        listen to you or not.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: Then the Spirit lifted me up, and I heard a loud rumbling sound behind
        me. (May the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> be praised in his place!)[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps> 
        </smallcaps>
      comments:
      - number: '3:12 '
        content: A possible reading for this verse is <b>Then the Spirit lifted me
          up, and as the glory of the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>
          rose from its place, I heard a loud rumbling sound behind me.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'It was the sound of the wings of the living beings as they brushed
        against each other and the rumbling of their wheels beneath them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Spirit lifted me up and took me away. I went in bitterness and
        turmoil, but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s hold on me was strong. "
      comments: []
    - title: A Watchman for Israel
      content: 'Then I came to the colony of Judean exiles in Tel-abib, beside the
        Kebar River. I was overwhelmed and sat among them for seven days.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After seven days the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave me a message.
        He said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, I have appointed you as a watchman for Israel.
        Whenever you receive a message from me, warn people immediately. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If I warn the wicked, saying, \u2018You are under the penalty of
        death,\u2019 but you fail to deliver the warning, they will die in their
        sins. And I will hold you responsible for their deaths. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you warn them and they refuse to repent and keep on sinning, they
        will die in their sins. But you will have saved yourself because you obeyed
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf righteous people turn away from their righteous behavior
        and ignore the obstacles I put in their way, they will die. And if you do
        not warn them, they will die in their sins. None of their righteous acts
        will be remembered, and I will hold you responsible for their deaths. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if you warn righteous people not to sin and they listen to you
        and do not sin, they will live, and you will have saved yourself, too.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> took hold of me and said, \u201CGet
        up and go out into the valley, and I will speak to you there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I got up and went, and there I saw the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        just as I had seen in my first vision by the Kebar River. And I fell face
        down on the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the Spirit came into me and set me on my feet. He spoke to me
        and said, \u201CGo to your house and shut yourself in. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There, son of man, you will be tied with ropes so you cannot go out
        among the people. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I will make your tongue stick to the roof of your mouth so that
        you will be speechless and unable to rebuke them, for they are rebels. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Sign of the Coming Siege
      content: "  \u201CAnd now, son of man, take a large clay brick and set it down
        in front of you. Then draw a map of the city of Jerusalem on it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Show the city under siege. Build a wall around it so no one can escape.
        Set up the enemy camp, and surround the city with siege ramps and battering
        rams. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then take an iron griddle and place it between you and the city.
        Turn toward the city and demonstrate how harsh the siege will be against
        Jerusalem. This will be a warning to the people of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow lie on your left side and place the sins of Israel on yourself.
        You are to bear their sins for the number of days you lie there on your side. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am requiring you to bear Israel\u2019s sins for 390 days\u2014one
        day for each year of their sin. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After that, turn over and lie on your right side for 40 days\u2014one
        day for each year of Judah\u2019s sin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMeanwhile, keep staring at the siege of Jerusalem. Lie there
        with your arm bared and prophesy her destruction. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will tie you up with ropes so you won\u2019t be able to turn from
        side to side until the days of your siege have been completed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow go and get some wheat, barley, beans, lentils, millet,
        and emmer wheat, and mix them together in a storage jar. Use them to make
        bread for yourself during the 390 days you will be lying on your side. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Ration this out to yourself, eight ounces[[COMMENT(0)]] of food for
        each day, and eat it at set times. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>20 shekels </b>[228 grams].
    - title: 
      content: 'Then measure out a jar[[COMMENT(0)]] of water for each day, and drink
        it at set times. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>1/6 of a hin </b>[about 1 pint or 0.6 liters].
    - title: 
      content: "Prepare and eat this food as you would barley cakes. While all the
        people are watching, bake it over a fire using dried human dung as fuel and
        then eat the bread.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CThis is how Israel
        will eat defiled bread in the Gentile lands to which I will banish them!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said, \u201CO Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, must
        I be defiled by using human dung? For I have never been defiled before. From
        the time I was a child until now I have never eaten any animal that died
        of sickness or was killed by other animals. I have never eaten any meat forbidden
        by the law.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll right,\u201D the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said. \u201CYou
        may bake your bread with cow dung instead of human dung.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he told me, \u201CSon of man, I will make food very scarce in
        Jerusalem. It will be weighed out with great care and eaten fearfully. The
        water will be rationed out drop by drop, and the people will drink it with
        dismay. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Sign of the Coming Judgment
      content: "  \u201CSon of man, take a sharp sword and use it as a razor to shave
        your head and beard. Use a scale to weigh the hair into three equal parts. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Place a third of it at the center of your map of Jerusalem. After
        acting out the siege, burn it there. Scatter another third across your map
        and chop it with a sword. Scatter the last third to the wind, for I will
        scatter my people with the sword. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Keep just a bit of the hair and tie it up in your robe. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then take some of these hairs out and throw them into the fire, burning
        them up. A fire will then spread from this remnant and destroy all of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:
        This is an illustration of what will happen to Jerusalem. I placed her at
        the center of the nations, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'but she has rebelled against my regulations and decrees and has been
        even more wicked than the surrounding nations. She has refused to obey the
        regulations and decrees I gave her to follow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: You people have behaved worse than your neighbors and have refused
        to obey my decrees and regulations. You have not even lived up to the standards
        of the nations around you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, I myself, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, am
        now your enemy. I will punish you publicly while all the nations watch. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because of your detestable idols, I will punish you like I have never
        punished anyone before or ever will again. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Parents will eat their own children, and children will eat their
        parents. I will punish you and scatter to the winds the few who survive.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAs surely as I live, says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        I will cut you off completely. I will show you no pity at all because you
        have defiled my Temple with your vile images and detestable sins. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A third of your people will die in the city from disease and famine.
        A third of them will be slaughtered by the enemy outside the city walls.
        And I will scatter a third to the winds, chasing them with my sword. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then at last my anger will be spent, and I will be satisfied. And
        when my fury against them has subsided, all Israel will know that I, the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken to them in my jealous anger.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo I will turn you into a ruin, a mockery in the eyes of the
        surrounding nations and to all who pass by. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will become an object of mockery and taunting and horror. You
        will be a warning to all the nations around you. They will see what happens
        when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> punishes a nation in anger and rebukes
        it, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will shower you with the deadly arrows of famine to destroy
        you. The famine will become more and more severe until every crumb of food
        is gone. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Judgment against Israel\u2019s Mountains"
      content: '  Again a message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, turn and face the mountains of Israel and prophesy
        against them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Proclaim this message from the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        against the mountains of Israel. This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says to the mountains and hills and to the ravines and valleys: I am about
        to bring war upon you, and I will smash your pagan shrines. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All your altars will be demolished, and your places of worship will
        be destroyed. I will kill your people in front of your idols.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:4 '
        content: The Hebrew term (literally <b>round things</b>) probably alludes
          to dung; also in 6:5, 6, 9, 13.
    - title: 
      content: 'I will lay your corpses in front of your idols and scatter your bones
        around your altars. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wherever you live there will be desolation, and I will destroy your
        pagan shrines. Your altars will be demolished, your idols will be smashed,
        your places of worship will be torn down, and all the religious objects you
        have made will be destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The place will be littered with corpses, and you will know that I
        alone am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut I will let a few of my people escape destruction, and they
        will be scattered among the nations of the world. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then when they are exiled among the nations, they will remember me.
        They will recognize how hurt I am by their unfaithful hearts and lustful
        eyes that long for their idols. Then at last they will hate themselves for
        all their detestable sins. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will know that I alone am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and
        that I was serious when I said I would bring this calamity on them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:
        Clap your hands in horror, and stamp your feet. Cry out because of all the
        detestable sins the people of Israel have committed. Now they are going to
        die from war and famine and disease. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Disease will strike down those who are far away in exile. War will
        destroy those who are nearby. And anyone who survives will be killed by famine.
        So at last I will spend my fury on them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> when their
        dead lie scattered among their idols and altars on every hill and mountain
        and under every green tree and every great shade tree\u2014the places where
        they offered sacrifices to their idols. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Coming of the End
      content: '  Then this message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says to Israel:\u201CThe end is here!Wherever you look\u2014east, west, north,
        or south\u2014your land is finished.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No hope remains,for I will unleash my anger against you.I will call
        you to accountfor all your detestable sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will turn my eyes away and show no pity.I will repay you for all
        your detestable sins.Then you will know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:Disaster
        after disasteris coming your way!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The end has come.It has finally arrived.Your final doom is waiting!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O people of Israel, the day of your destruction is dawning.The time
        has come; the day of trouble is near.Shouts of anguish will be heard on the
        mountains,not shouts of joy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Soon I will pour out my fury on youand unleash my anger against you.I
        will call you to accountfor all your detestable sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will turn my eyes away and show no pity.I will repay you for all
        your detestable sins.Then you will know that it is I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,who
        is striking the blow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe day of judgment is here;your destruction awaits!The people\u2019s
        wickedness and pridehave blossomed to full flower.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their violence has grown into a rodthat will beat them for their
        wickedness.None of these proud and wicked people will survive.All their wealth
        and prestige will be swept away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, the time has come;the day is here!Buyers should not rejoice
        over bargains,nor sellers grieve over losses,for all of them will fallunder
        my terrible anger.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Desolation of Israel
      content: "Even if the merchants survive,they will never return to their business.For
        what God has said applies to everyone\u2014it will not be changed!Not one
        person whose life is twisted by sinwill ever recover.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe trumpet calls Israel\u2019s army to mobilize,but no one
        listens,for my fury is against them all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There is war outside the cityand disease and famine within.Those
        outside the city wallswill be killed by enemy swords.Those inside the citywill
        die of famine and disease.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The survivors who escape to the mountainswill moan like doves, weeping
        for their sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their hands will hang limp,their knees will be weak as water.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will dress themselves in burlap;horror and shame will cover
        them.They will shave their headsin sorrow and remorse.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThey will throw their money in the streets,tossing it out like
        worthless trash.Their silver and gold won\u2019t save themon that day of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger.It will neither satisfy nor
        feed them,for their greed can only trip them up.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were proud of their beautiful jewelryand used it to make detestable
        idols and vile images.Therefore, I will make all their wealthdisgusting to
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will give it as plunder to foreigners,to the most wicked of nations,and
        they will defile it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will turn my eyes from themas these robbers invade and defile my
        treasured land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPrepare chains for my people,for the land is bloodied by terrible
        crimes.Jerusalem is filled with violence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will bring the most ruthless of nationsto occupy their homes.I
        will break down their proud fortressesand defile their sanctuaries.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Terror and trembling will overcome my people.They will look for peace
        but not find it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Calamity will follow calamity;rumor will follow rumor.They will look
        in vainfor a vision from the prophets.They will receive no teaching from
        the priestsand no counsel from the leaders.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Idolatry in the Temple
      content: "  Then on September 17,[[COMMENT(0)]] during the sixth year of King
        Jehoiachin\u2019s captivity, while the leaders of Judah were in my home,
        the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> took hold of me. "
      comments:
      - number: '8:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>on the fifth [day] of the sixth month, </b>of the ancient
          Hebrew lunar calendar. This event occurred on September 17, 592 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>;
          also see note on 1:1.
    - title: 
      content: 'I saw a figure that appeared to be a man.[[COMMENT(0)]] From what
        appeared to be his waist down, he looked like a burning flame. From the waist
        up he looked like gleaming amber.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:2a '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>appeared to be fire.</b>
      - number: '8:2b '
        content: Or <b>like burnished metal.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'He reached out what seemed to be a hand and took me by the hair.
        Then the Spirit lifted me up into the sky and transported me to Jerusalem
        in a vision from God. I was taken to the north gate of the inner courtyard
        of the Temple, where there is a large idol that has made the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        very jealous. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Suddenly, the glory of the God of Israel was there, just as I had
        seen it before in the valley.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CSon of man,
        look toward the north.\u201D So I looked, and there to the north, beside
        the entrance to the gate near the altar, stood the idol that had made the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> so jealous.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man,\u201D he said, \u201Cdo you see what they are doing?
        Do you see the detestable sins the people of Israel are committing to drive
        me from my Temple? But come, and you will see even more detestable sins than
        these!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then he brought me to the door of the Temple courtyard, where I could
        see a hole in the wall. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said to me, \u201CNow, son of man, dig into the wall.\u201D So
        I dug into the wall and found a hidden doorway.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo in,\u201D he said, \u201Cand see the wicked and detestable
        sins they are committing in there!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I went in and saw the walls covered with engravings of all kinds
        of crawling animals and detestable creatures. I also saw the various idols[[COMMENT(0)]]
        worshiped by the people of Israel. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:10 '
        content: The Hebrew term (literally <b>round things</b>) probably alludes
          to dung.
    - title: 
      content: 'Seventy leaders of Israel were standing there with Jaazaniah son
        of Shaphan in the center. Each of them held an incense burner, from which
        a cloud of incense rose above their heads.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CSon of man,
        have you seen what the leaders of Israel are doing with their idols in dark
        rooms? They are saying, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>doesn\u2019t
        see us; he has deserted our land!\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> added, \u201CCome, and I will
        show you even more detestable sins than these!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He brought me to the north gate of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Temple, and some women were sitting there, weeping for the god Tammuz. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave you seen this?\u201D he asked. \u201CBut I will show you
        even more detestable sins than these!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he brought me into the inner courtyard of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        Temple. At the entrance to the sanctuary, between the entry room and the
        bronze altar, there were about twenty-five men with their backs to the sanctuary
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. They were facing east, bowing low to
        the ground, worshiping the sun!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHave you seen this, son of man?\u201D he asked. \u201CIs it
        nothing to the people of Judah that they commit these detestable sins, leading
        the whole nation into violence, thumbing their noses at me, and provoking
        my anger? "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Slaughter of Idolaters
      content: "  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> thundered, \u201CBring on
        the men appointed to punish the city! Tell them to bring their weapons with
        them!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Six men soon appeared from the upper gate that faces north, each
        carrying a deadly weapon in his hand. With them was a man dressed in linen,
        who carried a writer\u2019s case at his side. They all went into the Temple
        courtyard and stood beside the bronze altar.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the glory of the God of Israel rose up from between the cherubim,
        where it had rested, and moved to the entrance of the Temple. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        called to the man dressed in linen who was carrying the writer\u2019s case. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said to him, \u201CWalk through the streets of Jerusalem and put
        a mark on the foreheads of all who weep and sigh because of the detestable
        sins being committed in their city.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I heard the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> say to the other men,
        \u201CFollow him through the city and kill everyone whose forehead is not
        marked. Show no mercy; have no pity! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Kill them all\u2014old and young, girls and women and little children.
        But do not touch anyone with the mark. Begin right here at the Temple.\u201D
        So they began by killing the seventy leaders.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDefile the Temple!\u201D the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded.
        \u201CFill its courtyards with corpses. Go!\u201D So they went and began
        killing throughout the city.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "While they were out killing, I was all alone. I fell face down on
        the ground and cried out, \u201CO Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!
        Will your fury against Jerusalem wipe out everyone left in Israel?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said to me, \u201CThe sins of the people of Israel and Judah
        are very, very great. The entire land is full of murder; the city is filled
        with injustice. They are saying, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>doesn\u2019t
        see it! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has abandoned the land!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will not spare them or have any pity on them. I will fully repay
        them for all they have done.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Glory Leaves the Temple"
      content: '  In my vision I saw what appeared to be a throne of blue lapis lazuli
        above the crystal surface over the heads of the cherubim. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to the man in linen clothing
        and said, \u201CGo between the whirling wheels beneath the cherubim, and
        take a handful of burning coals and scatter them over the city.\u201D He
        did this as I watched.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The cherubim were standing at the south end of the Temple when the
        man went in, and the cloud of glory filled the inner courtyard. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rose up from above
        the cherubim and went over to the entrance of the Temple. The Temple was
        filled with this cloud of glory, and the courtyard glowed brightly with the
        glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The moving wings of the cherubim sounded like the voice of God Almighty[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and could be heard even in the outer courtyard.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>El-Shaddai.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to the man in linen clothing,
        \u201CGo between the cherubim and take some burning coals from between the
        wheels.\u201D So the man went in and stood beside one of the wheels. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then one of the cherubim reached out his hand and took some live
        coals from the fire burning among them. He put the coals into the hands of
        the man in linen clothing, and the man took them and went out. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '(All the cherubim had what looked like human hands under their wings.)  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I looked, and each of the four cherubim had a wheel beside him, and
        the wheels sparkled like beryl. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All four wheels looked alike and were made the same; each wheel had
        a second wheel turning crosswise within it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The cherubim could move in any of the four directions they faced,
        without turning as they moved. They went straight in the direction they faced,
        never turning aside. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Both the cherubim and the wheels were covered with eyes. The cherubim
        had eyes all over their bodies, including their hands, their backs, and their
        wings. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I heard someone refer to the wheels as \u201Cthe whirling wheels.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Each of the four cherubim had four faces: the first was the face
        of an ox,[[COMMENT(0)]] the second was a human face, the third was the face
        of a lion, and the fourth was the face of an eagle.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the face of a cherub; </b>compare 1:10.
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the cherubim rose upward. These were the same living beings
        I had seen beside the Kebar River. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the cherubim moved, the wheels moved with them. When they lifted
        their wings to fly, the wheels stayed beside them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the cherubim stopped, the wheels stopped. When they flew upward,
        the wheels rose up, for the spirit of the living beings was in the wheels.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> moved out from
        the entrance of the Temple and hovered above the cherubim. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And as I watched, the cherubim flew with their wheels to the east
        gate of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Temple. And the glory of the
        God of Israel hovered above them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These were the same living beings I had seen beneath the God of Israel
        when I was by the Kebar River. I knew they were cherubim, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for each had four faces and four wings and what looked like human
        hands under their wings. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Judgment on Israel\u2019s Leaders"
      content: "  Then the Spirit lifted me and brought me to the east gateway of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Temple, where I saw twenty-five prominent
        men of the city. Among them were Jaazaniah son of Azzur and Pelatiah son
        of Benaiah, who were leaders among the people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Spirit said to me, \u201CSon of man, these are the men who are
        planning evil and giving wicked counsel in this city. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They say to the people, \u2018Is it not a good time to build houses?
        This city is like an iron pot. We are safe inside it like meat in a pot.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '11:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>This city is the pot, and we are the meat.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, son of man, prophesy against them loudly and clearly.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came upon me,
        and he told me to say, \u201CThis is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says to the people of Israel: I know what you are saying, for I know every
        thought that comes into your minds. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have murdered many in this city and filled its streets with the
        dead.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: This city is an iron pot all right, but the pieces of meat are the
        victims of your injustice. As for you, I will soon drag you from this pot. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will bring on you the sword of war you so greatly fear, says the
        Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will drive you out of Jerusalem and hand you over to foreigners,
        who will carry out my judgments against you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will be slaughtered all the way to the borders of Israel. I will
        execute judgment on you, and you will know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, this city will not be an iron pot for you, and you will not be
        like meat safe inside it. I will judge you even to the borders of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and you will know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. For
        you have refused to obey my decrees and regulations; instead, you have copied
        the standards of the nations around you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Hope for Exiled Israel
      content: "While I was still prophesying, Pelatiah son of Benaiah suddenly died.
        Then I fell face down on the ground and cried out, \u201CO Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        are you going to kill everyone in Israel?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then this message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, the people still left in Jerusalem are talking
        about you and your relatives and all the people of Israel who are in exile.
        They are saying, \u2018Those people are far away from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        so now he has given their land to us!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, tell the exiles, \u2018This is what the Sovereign
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Although I have scattered you in the countries
        of the world, I will be a sanctuary to you during your time in exile. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, will gather you back
        from the nations where you have been scattered, and I will give you the land
        of Israel once again.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen the people return to their homeland, they will remove
        every trace of their vile images and detestable idols. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I will give them singleness of heart and put a new spirit within
        them. I will take away their stony, stubborn heart and give them a tender,
        responsive heart,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>a heart of flesh.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'so they will obey my decrees and regulations. Then they will truly
        be my people, and I will be their God. '
      comments: []
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Glory Leaves Jerusalem"
      content: "But as for those who long for vile images and detestable idols, I
        will repay them fully for their sins. I, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the cherubim lifted their wings and rose into the air with their
        wheels beside them, and the glory of the God of Israel hovered above them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> went up from the
        city and stopped above the mountain to the east.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Afterward the Spirit of God carried me back again to Babylonia,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to the people in exile there. And so ended the vision of my visit to Jerusalem. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:24 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldea.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: Signs of the Coming Exile
      content: '  Again a message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, you live among rebels who have eyes but refuse
        to see. They have ears but refuse to hear. For they are a rebellious people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo now, son of man, pretend you are being sent into exile.
        Pack the few items an exile could carry, and leave your home to go somewhere
        else. Do this right in front of the people so they can see you. For perhaps
        they will pay attention to this, even though they are such rebels. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Bring your baggage outside during the day so they can watch you.
        Then in the evening, as they are watching, leave your house as captives do
        when they begin a long march to distant lands. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Dig a hole through the wall while they are watching and go out through
        it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As they watch, lift your pack to your shoulders and walk away into
        the night. Cover your face so you cannot see the land you are leaving. For
        I have made you a sign for the people of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I did as I was told. In broad daylight I brought my pack outside,
        filled with the things I might carry into exile. Then in the evening while
        the people looked on, I dug through the wall with my hands and went out into
        the night with my pack on my shoulder.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The next morning this message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, these rebels, the people of Israel, have asked
        you what all this means. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Say to them, \u2018This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: These actions contain a message for King Zedekiah in Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and for all the people of Israel.\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '12:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the prince in Jerusalem; </b>similarly in 12:12.
    - title: 
      content: 'Explain that your actions are a sign to show what will soon happen
        to them, for they will be driven into exile as captives.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEven Zedekiah will leave Jerusalem at night through a hole
        in the wall, taking only what he can carry with him. He will cover his face,
        and his eyes will not see the land he is leaving. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I will throw my net over him and capture him in my snare. I
        will bring him to Babylon, the land of the Babylonians,[[COMMENT(0)]] though
        he will never see it, and he will die there. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:13 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I will scatter his servants and warriors to the four winds and send
        the sword after them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And when I scatter them among the nations, they will know that I
        am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I will spare a few of them from death by war, famine, or disease,
        so they can confess all their detestable sins to their captors. Then they
        will know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then this message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, tremble as you eat your food. Shake with fear as
        you drink your water. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Tell the people, \u2018This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says concerning those living in Israel and Jerusalem: They will eat their
        food with trembling and sip their water in despair, for their land will be
        stripped bare because of their violence. "
      comments: []
    - title: A New Proverb for Israel
      content: "The cities will be destroyed and the farmland made desolate. Then
        you will know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Again a message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, you\u2019ve heard that proverb they quote in Israel:
        \u2018Time passes, and prophecies come to nothing.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Tell the people, \u2018This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: I will put an end to this proverb, and you will soon stop quoting it.\u2019
        Now give them this new proverb to replace the old one: \u2018The time has
        come for every prophecy to be fulfilled!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThere will be no more false visions and flattering predictions
        in Israel. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>! If I say it, it will happen.
        There will be no more delays, you rebels of Israel. I will fulfill my threat
        of destruction in your own lifetime. I, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then this message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, the people of Israel are saying, \u2018He\u2019s
        talking about the distant future. His visions won\u2019t come true for a
        long, long time.\u2019 "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Judgment against False Prophets
      content: '  Then this message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, prophesy against the false prophets of Israel who
        are inventing their own prophecies. Say to them, \u2018Listen to the word
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: What
        sorrow awaits the false prophets who are following their own imaginations
        and have seen nothing at all!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO people of Israel, these prophets of yours are like jackals
        digging in the ruins. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have done nothing to repair the breaks in the walls around the
        nation. They have not helped it to stand firm in battle on the day of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Instead, they have told lies and made false predictions. They say,
        \u2018This message is from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u2019 even though
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> never sent them. And yet they expect him
        to fulfill their prophecies! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Can your visions be anything but false if you claim, \u2018This message
        is from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u2019 when I have not even spoken
        to you?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: Because what you say is false and your visions are a lie, I will stand
        against you, says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will raise my fist against all the prophets who see false visions
        and make lying predictions, and they will be banished from the community
        of Israel. I will blot their names from Israel\u2019s record books, and they
        will never again set foot in their own land. Then you will know that I am
        the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis will happen because these evil prophets deceive my people
        by saying, \u2018All is peaceful\u2019 when there is no peace at all! It\u2019s
        as if the people have built a flimsy wall, and these prophets are trying
        to reinforce it by covering it with whitewash! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Tell these whitewashers that their wall will soon fall down. A heavy
        rainstorm will undermine it; great hailstones and mighty winds will knock
        it down. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And when the wall falls, the people will cry out, \u2018What happened
        to your whitewash?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: I will sweep away your whitewashed wall with a storm of indignation,
        with a great flood of anger, and with hailstones of fury. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will break down your wall right to its foundation, and when it
        falls, it will crush you. Then you will know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At last my anger against the wall and those who covered it with whitewash
        will be satisfied. Then I will say to you: \u2018The wall and those who whitewashed
        it are both gone. "
      comments: []
    - title: Judgment against False Women Prophets
      content: "They were lying prophets who claimed peace would come to Jerusalem
        when there was no peace. I, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have
        spoken!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow, son of man, speak out against the women who prophesy from
        their own imaginations. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: What
        sorrow awaits you women who are ensnaring the souls of my people, young and
        old alike. You tie magic charms on their wrists and furnish them with magic
        veils. Do you think you can trap others without bringing destruction on yourselves? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You bring shame on me among my people for a few handfuls of barley
        or a piece of bread. By lying to my people who love to listen to lies, you
        kill those who should not die, and you promise life to those who should not
        live.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:
        I am against all your magic charms, which you use to ensnare my people like
        birds. I will tear them from your arms, setting my people free like birds
        set free from a cage. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will tear off the magic veils and save my people from your grasp.
        They will no longer be your victims. Then you will know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have discouraged the righteous with your lies, but I didn\u2019t
        want them to be sad. And you have encouraged the wicked by promising them
        life, even though they continue in their sins. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The Idolatry of Israel\u2019s Leaders"
      content: '  Then some of the leaders of Israel visited me, and while they were
        sitting with me, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'this message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, these leaders have set up idols[[COMMENT(0)]] in
        their hearts. They have embraced things that will make them fall into sin.
        Why should I listen to their requests? "
      comments:
      - number: '14:3 '
        content: The Hebrew term (literally <b>round things</b>) probably alludes
          to dung; also in 14:4, 5, 6, 7.
    - title: 
      content: "Tell them, \u2018This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: The people of Israel have set up idols in their hearts and fallen into
        sin, and then they go to a prophet asking for a message. So I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        will give them the kind of answer their great idolatry deserves. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will do this to capture the minds and hearts of all my people who
        have turned from me to worship their detestable idols.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, tell the people of Israel, \u2018This is what the
        Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Repent and turn away from your
        idols, and stop all your detestable sins. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, will answer all those, both Israelites
        and foreigners, who reject me and set up idols in their hearts and so fall
        into sin, and who then come to a prophet asking for my advice. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will turn against such people and make a terrible example of them,
        eliminating them from among my people. Then you will know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018And if a prophet is deceived into giving a message, it
        is because I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have deceived that prophet.
        I will lift my fist against such prophets and cut them off from the community
        of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'False prophets and those who seek their guidance will all be punished
        for their sins. '
      comments: []
    - title: "The Certainty of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Judgment"
      content: "In this way, the people of Israel will learn not to stray from me,
        polluting themselves with sin. They will be my people, and I will be their
        God. I, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then this message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, suppose the people of a country were to sin against
        me, and I lifted my fist to crush them, cutting off their food supply and
        sending a famine to destroy both people and animals. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even if Noah, Daniel, and Job were there, their righteousness would
        save no one but themselves, says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COr suppose I were to send wild animals to invade the country,
        kill the people, and make the land too desolate and dangerous to pass through. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As surely as I live, says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        even if those three men were there, they wouldn\u2019t be able to save their
        own sons or daughters. They alone would be saved, but the land would be made
        desolate.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COr suppose I were to bring war against the land, and I sent
        enemy armies to destroy both people and animals. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As surely as I live, says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        even if those three men were there, they wouldn\u2019t be able to save their
        own sons or daughters. They alone would be saved.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COr suppose I were to pour out my fury by sending an epidemic
        into the land, and the disease killed people and animals alike. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As surely as I live, says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        even if Noah, Daniel, and Job were there, they wouldn\u2019t be able to save
        their own sons or daughters. They alone would be saved by their righteousness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: How terrible it will be when all four of these dreadful punishments
        fall upon Jerusalem\u2014war, famine, wild animals, and disease\u2014destroying
        all her people and animals. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet there will be survivors, and they will come here to join you
        as exiles in Babylon. You will see with your own eyes how wicked they are,
        and then you will feel better about what I have done to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Jerusalem\u2014a Useless Vine"
      content: '  Then this message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, how does a grapevine compare to a tree? Is a vine\u2019s
        wood as useful as the wood of a tree? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can its wood be used for making things, like pegs to hang up pots
        and pans? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, it can only be used for fuel, and even as fuel, it burns too
        quickly. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Vines are useless both before and after being put into the fire!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: The people of Jerusalem are like grapevines growing among the trees
        of the forest. Since they are useless, I have thrown them on the fire to
        be burned. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I will see to it that if they escape from one fire, they will
        fall into another. When I turn against them, you will know that I am the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Jerusalem\u2014an Unfaithful Wife"
      content: '  Then another message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, confront Jerusalem with her detestable sins. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give her this message from the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:
        You are nothing but a Canaanite! Your father was an Amorite and your mother
        a Hittite. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On the day you were born, no one cared about you. Your umbilical
        cord was not cut, and you were never washed, rubbed with salt, and wrapped
        in cloth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No one had the slightest interest in you; no one pitied you or cared
        for you. On the day you were born, you were unwanted, dumped in a field and
        left to die.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut I came by and saw you there, helplessly kicking about in
        your own blood. As you lay there, I said, \u2018Live!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I helped you to thrive like a plant in the field. You grew up
        and became a beautiful jewel. Your breasts became full, and your body hair
        grew, but you were still naked. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And when I passed by again, I saw that you were old enough for love.
        So I wrapped my cloak around you to cover your nakedness and declared my
        marriage vows. I made a covenant with you, says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and you became mine.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen I bathed you and washed off your blood, and I rubbed fragrant
        oils into your skin. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I gave you expensive clothing of fine linen and silk, beautifully
        embroidered, and sandals made of fine goatskin leather. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I gave you lovely jewelry, bracelets, beautiful necklaces, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'a ring for your nose, earrings for your ears, and a lovely crown
        for your head. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And so you were adorned with gold and silver. Your clothes were made
        of fine linen and costly fabric and were beautifully embroidered. You ate
        the finest foods\u2014choice flour, honey, and olive oil\u2014and became
        more beautiful than ever. You looked like a queen, and so you were! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your fame soon spread throughout the world because of your beauty.
        I dressed you in my splendor and perfected your beauty, says the Sovereign
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you thought your fame and beauty were your own. So you
        gave yourself as a prostitute to every man who came along. Your beauty was
        theirs for the asking. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You used the lovely things I gave you to make shrines for idols,
        where you played the prostitute. Unbelievable! How could such a thing ever
        happen? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You took the very jewels and gold and silver ornaments I had given
        you and made statues of men and worshiped them. This is adultery against
        me! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You used the beautifully embroidered clothes I gave you to dress
        your idols. Then you used my special oil and my incense to worship them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Imagine it! You set before them as a sacrifice the choice flour,
        olive oil, and honey I had given you, says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen you took your sons and daughters\u2014the children you
        had borne to me\u2014and sacrificed them to your gods. Was your prostitution
        not enough? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Must you also slaughter my children by sacrificing them to idols? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In all your years of adultery and detestable sin, you have not once
        remembered the days long ago when you lay naked in a field, kicking about
        in your own blood.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat sorrow awaits you, says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        In addition to all your other wickedness, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'you built a pagan shrine and put altars to idols in every town square. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On every street corner you defiled your beauty, offering your body
        to every passerby in an endless stream of prostitution. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you added lustful Egypt to your lovers, provoking my anger with
        your increasing promiscuity. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That is why I struck you with my fist and reduced your boundaries.
        I handed you over to your enemies, the Philistines, and even they were shocked
        by your lewd conduct. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have prostituted yourself with the Assyrians, too. It seems you
        can never find enough new lovers! And after your prostitution there, you
        still were not satisfied. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You added to your lovers by embracing Babylonia,[[COMMENT(0)]] the
        land of merchants, but you still weren\u2019t satisfied.  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:29 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldea.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat a sick heart you have, says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        to do such things as these, acting like a shameless prostitute. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You build your pagan shrines on every street corner and your altars
        to idols in every square. In fact, you have been worse than a prostitute,
        so eager for sin that you have not even demanded payment. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, you are an adulterous wife who takes in strangers instead of
        her own husband. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Prostitutes charge for their services\u2014but not you! You give
        gifts to your lovers, bribing them to come and have sex with you. "
      comments: []
    - title: "Judgment on Jerusalem\u2019s Prostitution"
      content: 'So you are the opposite of other prostitutes. You pay your lovers
        instead of their paying you!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTherefore, you prostitute, listen to this message from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Because
        you have poured out your lust and exposed yourself in prostitution to all
        your lovers, and because you have worshiped detestable idols,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and because you have slaughtered your children as sacrifices to your gods, '
      comments:
      - number: '16:36 '
        content: The Hebrew term (literally <b>round things</b>) probably alludes
          to dung.
    - title: 
      content: "this is what I am going to do. I will gather together all your allies\u2014the
        lovers with whom you have sinned, both those you loved and those you hated\u2014and
        I will strip you naked in front of them so they can stare at you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will punish you for your murder and adultery. I will cover you
        with blood in my jealous fury. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then I will give you to these many nations who are your lovers, and
        they will destroy you. They will knock down your pagan shrines and the altars
        to your idols. They will strip you and take your beautiful jewels, leaving
        you stark naked. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will band together in a mob to stone you and cut you up with
        swords. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will burn your homes and punish you in front of many women.
        I will stop your prostitution and end your payments to your many lovers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen at last my fury against you will be spent, and my jealous
        anger will subside. I will be calm and will not be angry with you anymore. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But first, because you have not remembered your youth but have angered
        me by doing all these evil things, I will fully repay you for all of your
        sins, says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. For you have added
        lewd acts to all your detestable sins. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Everyone who makes up proverbs will say of you, \u2018Like mother,
        like daughter.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For your mother loathed her husband and her children, and so do you.
        And you are exactly like your sisters, for they despised their husbands and
        their children. Truly your mother was a Hittite and your father an Amorite.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYour older sister was Samaria, who lived with her daughters
        in the north. Your younger sister was Sodom, who lived with her daughters
        in the south. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you have not merely sinned as they did. You quickly surpassed
        them in corruption. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As surely as I live, says the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        Sodom and her daughters were never as wicked as you and your daughters. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Sodom\u2019s sins were pride, gluttony, and laziness, while the poor
        and needy suffered outside her door. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'She was proud and committed detestable sins, so I wiped her out,
        as you have seen.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:50 '
        content: As in a few Hebrew manuscripts and Greek version; Masoretic Text
          reads <b>as I have seen.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEven Samaria did not commit half your sins. You have done far
        more detestable things than your sisters ever did. They seem righteous compared
        to you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Shame on you! Your sins are so terrible that you make your sisters
        seem righteous, even virtuous.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut someday I will restore the fortunes of Sodom and Samaria,
        and I will restore you, too. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you will be truly ashamed of everything you have done, for your
        sins make them feel good in comparison. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, your sisters, Sodom and Samaria, and all their people will be
        restored, and at that time you also will be restored. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In your proud days you held Sodom in contempt. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But now your greater wickedness has been exposed to all the world,
        and you are the one who is scorned\u2014by Edom[[COMMENT(0)]] and all her
        neighbors and by Philistia. "
      comments:
      - number: '16:57 '
        content: As in many Hebrew manuscripts and Syriac version; Masoretic Text
          reads <b>Aram.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'This is your punishment for all your lewdness and detestable sins,
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says: I will give you what you deserve, for you have taken your solemn vows
        lightly by breaking your covenant. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet I will remember the covenant I made with you when you were young,
        and I will establish an everlasting covenant with you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then you will remember with shame all the evil you have done. I will
        make your sisters, Samaria and Sodom, to be your daughters, even though they
        are not part of our covenant. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I will reaffirm my covenant with you, and you will know that
        I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Story of Two Eagles
      content: '  Then this message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSon of man, give this riddle, and tell this story to the people
        of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Give them this message from the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:\u201CA
        great eagle with broad wings and long feathers,covered with many-colored
        plumage,came to Lebanon.He seized the top of a cedar tree  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and plucked off its highest branch.He carried it away to a city filled
        with merchants.He planted it in a city of traders.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He also took a seedling from the landand planted it in fertile soil.He
        placed it beside a broad river,where it could grow like a willow tree.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It took root thereand grew into a low, spreading vine.Its branches
        turned up toward the eagle,and its roots grew down into the ground.It produced
        strong branchesand put out shoots.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But then another great eagle camewith broad wings and full plumage.So
        the vine now sent its roots and branchestoward him for water,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'even though it was already planted in good soiland had plenty of
        waterso it could grow into a splendid vineand produce rich leaves and luscious
        fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSo now the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> asks:Will
        this vine grow and prosper?No! I will pull it up, roots and all!I will cut
        off its fruitand let its leaves wither and die.I will pull it up easilywithout
        a strong arm or a large army.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Riddle Explained
      content: "But when the vine is transplanted,will it thrive?No, it will wither
        awaywhen the east wind blows against it.It will die in the same good soilwhere
        it had grown so well.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then this message came to me from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSay to these rebels of Israel: Don\u2019t you understand the
        meaning of this riddle of the eagles? The king of Babylon came to Jerusalem,
        took away her king and princes, and brought them to Babylon. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He made a treaty with a member of the royal family and forced him
        to take an oath of loyalty. He also exiled Israel\u2019s most influential
        leaders, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'so Israel would not become strong again and revolt. Only by keeping
        her treaty with Babylon could Israel survive.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNevertheless, this man of Israel\u2019s royal family rebelled
